ENTRY            C3101   20260115   20260312   20260312       C253
SUBENT        C3101001   20260115   20260312   20260312       C253
BIB                 10         29
TITLE      Neutron Spectra from Deuteron and Proton Bombardment
           of Thick Lithium Targets
AUTHOR     (C.E.Nelson,F.O.Purser,P.Von Behren,H.W.Newson)
INSTITUTE  (1USATNL)
REFERENCE  (R,NBSIR-77-1279,1,1977)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USATNL) The Triangle Universities Nuclear
           Laboratory Model FN Tandem Van de Graaff accelerator
           was used in conjunction with the TUNL neutron
           time-off light facility.
INC-SPECT  Beam currents of 2-5 nA with a time resolution of 1.5
           to 2.0 nsec were used.
DETECTOR   (SCIN) The neutron detector consisted of a 8.89 cm
           diameter by 5.04 cm thick NE 218 liquid scintillator
           coupled to a 56 DVP photomultiplier.
SAMPLE     (3-LI-7,ENR=0.9999) The lithium target was enriched
           to 99.99% 7Li and was encapsulated in an aluminum
           container under a helium atmosphere. The upstream
           face of the lithium was covered with a 3.5 pm
           molybdenum foil and the target length was 1.9 cm,
           sufficient to stop 15 MeV deuterons.
METHOD     (TOF,PSD) Neutron energy spectra and yields produced
           by the bombardment of thick lithium targets by
           deuterons and protons have been measured using the
           time-of-flight method. Measurements were made at
           angles up to 45 degree for deuteron energies of 8, 12
           and 15 MeV and a proton energy of 15 MeV. Pulse shape
           discrimination was used to discriminate against gamma
           ray events.
HISTORY    (20260115C) BP
ENDBIB              29
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           32
